# SELinux policy for the Cuttlefish e1_npu sim overlay.
#
# The hal_e1_npu_default domain and dev_type are defined in
# device/eliza/eliza_ai_soc/sepolicy/e1_npu.te. We do NOT redefine
# them here. The sim binary does not touch /dev/e1-npu (no kernel
# node under Cuttlefish), so the sim path requires no additional
# rules beyond what the base policy already grants for binder/log.
#
# This file exists so BOARD_VENDOR_SEPOLICY_DIRS resolves to a real
# directory at build time.
